            <h5 class="column-head feature" data-uuid="55d18859137843a186f50ed2d7e173e0">Agricultural
                Supply and Demand</h5>
            <p class="intro-feature" data-uuid="d7e7fd2079ad4e7c98cc09b7ce4a04ea">In the late 1800s Plains farmers experienced hard times, some of
                which followed big harvests. How did good harvests create hard times? The
                answer is the law of supply and demand.&#160;The
                amount of goods available for sale is the <b>supply</b>.
                The willingness and ability of consumers to buy goods is called <b>demand</b>.<b> </b>The law of supply and demand
                says that when supply increases or demand decreases, prices fall. By contrast,
                when supply decreases or demand rises, prices rise.</p>
            <article class="column-container" data-uuid="33942a2e79894795bb652f56ff5b1f7d">
