        <p data-uuid="1fe3dfaa59e44d11999fdde1210c986e">The Populists had to decide between running their own candidate, and thus splitting the silver vote, and supporting Bryan. They decided to support Bryan. The Republicans had a well-financed campaign, and they won the election. McKinley‘s victory in 1896 marked the end of both the Populist Party and the Farmers’ Alliances.<br />
        </p>
